    "body": "Independent review: CHANGES REQUIRED before integration.\n\n1. Scope violation: `plugins/asynchronia/model_selector.py` is changed even though the authorized task explicitly forbade this path and required `BLOCKED_SCOPE_COLLISION` if a selector-source change was necessary. The current patch changes `MAINTENANCE_TASK_ID`, `confirmed_timestamp`, and `supersedes`. These changes may be technically necessary, but they require explicit narrow scope expansion rather than silent mutation.\n\n2. Incorrect future timestamp: the task artifacts and selector snapshot use `2026-07-22T15:29:00+09:00` / `2026-07-22T06:29:00Z`, while the user confirmation occurred around `2026-07-22 02:36 JST`. The recorded confirmation time must not be in the future and must match the actual confirmation event.\n\n3. PR description is inconsistent with the diff: it says `Selector scoring/routing logic changes: none`, but `MAINTENANCE_TASK_ID` is an active maintenance-routing constant and is changed in this PR. Update the description and task evidence to state the exact minimal selector-source change.\n\nDo not merge. Correct the existing branch/PR with an explicitly authorized narrow scope expansion for `plugins/asynchronia/model_selector.py`, fix timestamp/provenance consistently across inventory/task artifacts, snapshot, generator constants, tests, and generated hash, rerun validations and the temporary 23/23 selector proof, then return for independent re-review.",
